						<summary>

						<p>Slab in a locality called Khaṇḍāri.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla [Vikramāditya VI] 1113 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This, a little damaged record, speaks of the rule of Chālukya Tribhuvanamalla. It records the grant of 35 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of land to the west of the village by the <hi rend="italic">mahājanas</hi> and 40 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of land to the east (of the village) by the queen Chandaladēvi, to the god Kēśavadēva of <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> Poḷagunḍe which is stated to be a bhattagrāma of the queen. </p>						

						<p>The record is dated in the Chālukya Vikrama year 37, Śaka 1035, Vijaya, Bhādrapada, śu. lunar eclipse. It corresponds to 1113 A.D., August. 28 [Thursday]. Lunar eclipse occured on that day.</p>						

						</summary>
